    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to works produced since the 1960s that employ the artists own body, or other people's bodies, as the medium of expression. May be in the form of performance art or conceptual art, where the artist uses his or her own body as a focus or theme. For visual works that are body modifications based on traditional or ancient practices, such as scarification or tattooing, prefer "body art (visual works, adornment)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046448/Oxford Dictionary of Art (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para obras producidas desde 1960 que emplean cuerpos humanos como medio de expresión; puede ser en la forma de arte de performance o que el artista utiliza su propio cuerpo como foco o tema.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar werken, gemaakt vanaf de jaren 60 van de 20ste eeuw, waarin het menselijk lichaam wordt gebruikt als belangrijkste expressiemiddel. Dit kan zijn in de vorm van een performance of in een vorm waarbij de kunstenaar het eigen lichaam gebruikt als middelpunt of thema. Zie 'lichaamskunst' voor de tak van beeldende kunsten waarbij decoraties en versieringen worden aangebracht op het menselijk lichaam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於1960年代起開始創作的作品，運用人類身體做為表現媒介；有可能以表演藝術的形式展現，或藝術家把自己的身體當作焦點或主題。若指稱與人體裝飾及美化有關的視覺藝術類別，則使用「身體藝術」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Werk, produziert seit den 1960er Jahren, das den menschlichen Körper als Ausdrucksmittel benutzt; may be in the form of performance art, or the artist using his own body as a focus or theme. Für den Zweig der visuellen Künste, die die Dekoration und Verschönerung des menschlichen Körpers betreffen, siehe "[body arts](300386734)" For the branch of the visual arts involving the decoration and embellishment of the human body see "body arts."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
